---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Lingoda Review 2026: The Best Online Language School?" description="A structured online school with small group classes. Best for learners who want a traditional classroom feel with modern flexibility.">
<article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">Review · Updated April 2026</span>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-1 mb-4">Lingoda Review 2026: The Best Online Language School?</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500">A structured online school with small group classes. Best for learners who want a traditional classroom feel with modern flexibility.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-lg text-emerald-900">Our Rating</p>
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-700">8.8/10</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-right">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Best for</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-700">Structured group classes</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What is Lingoda?</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lingoda is an online language school that offers small group classes led by native-level teachers. Unlike marketplaces where you choose your own teacher, Lingoda provides a structured curriculum aligned with the CEFR standards (A1 to C1). Classes are available 24/7, making it easy to fit into any schedule.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Pricing</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lingoda operates on a monthly subscription model. Prices vary depending on the frequency of your classes, but you can expect to pay between $10 and $15 per group class. They are also famous for their "Sprint" promotions, which offer significant cashback if you attend every class in your plan.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Pros</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>CEFR-aligned curriculum with downloadable materials</li>
    <li>Small class sizes (usually 3 to 5 students)</li>
    <li>Excellent "Sprint" challenges for high motivation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Cons</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>You cannot always choose the same teacher for every class</li>
    <li>Group dynamics can sometimes be unpredictable</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Verdict</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lingoda is perfect for students who need a clear path and a structured syllabus. It feels more like a real school than a marketplace, and the quality of instruction is consistently high across the board.</p>

  <div class="bg-emerald-600 rounded-xl p-8 text-white mt-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Join a class today</h3>
    <p class="mb-6">Start your structured learning journey with Lingoda. Group classes start at $10.</p>
    <a href="https://www.lingoda.com/" class="bg-white text-emerald-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">Visit Lingoda</a>
  </div>
</article>
</Base>
